I would reccomend this to anyone who likes 2D puzzle games, as even I don't like puzzle games as much as games with brutal combat, but I still enjoy this very much. The antithesis of "all flash no substance," this game trades flash for simplicity, and uses that simplicity to craft a very good game.

I love the concept of the game, but there are a few problems,  and sadly they're big ones.   1. No checkpoints. Even when you get to the very end of a level after 3 minutes of the level, when you die, you go back all the way to the beginning and have to do it all over again, it gets tedious quickly.   2. No erasers. All it gives you is an undo button. For drawing tools and fire and all,  this isn't an issue. But when drawing your character and friend, it gets very annoying. Speaking of friend...   3. No re-drawing your friend. There is no way to re-draw the friend without re-drawing yourself, so if you like your character and not your friend, or accidentally hit confirm when the friend isn't complete, well to bad.   I really like the concept,  but it just got to frustrating because of these issues.
